<quantity box="[953,1018,1133,1160]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
, TW= 1.8 mm. Body stiffed, long, narrowed posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[356,456,1169,1195]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,181,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-26@30.[236,1352,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A) Complete fragmented body. B) Drawing of prostomium, dorsal view. C) Drawing of prostomium, ventral view. D) Prostomium, dorsal view. E) Prostomium, ventral view; arrow indicates Mo. F) Right side of middle segments, arrow indicates dorsal cirrus. G) Dorsal side of the specimen, showing the middorsal line paleae free. H) Parapodium from segment 49. I) Lateral paleae. J) Subunit 1. K) Main palea, arrow indicates finely raised rib. Scales: 20 µm (IJK), 100 µm (BCDEFH), 500 µm (G), 1 mm (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702063/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). Body orange to brown, dorsal and ventral cirri bases darker (
<figureCitation box="[1134,1234,1169,1195]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,181,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-26@30.[236,1352,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A) Complete fragmented body. B) Drawing of prostomium, dorsal view. C) Drawing of prostomium, ventral view. D) Prostomium, dorsal view. E) Prostomium, ventral view; arrow indicates Mo. F) Right side of middle segments, arrow indicates dorsal cirrus. G) Dorsal side of the specimen, showing the middorsal line paleae free. H) Parapodium from segment 49. I) Lateral paleae. J) Subunit 1. K) Main palea, arrow indicates finely raised rib. Scales: 20 µm (IJK), 100 µm (BCDEFH), 500 µm (G), 1 mm (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702063/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 14G</figureCitation>
). Paleae fan bright maroon to golden, non-imbricated dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,881,2024]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Prostomium retracted among the first four segments. Lateral antennae long, inserted on antero-ventral prostomial margin, median antenna slightly shorter than lateral ones, inserted in front of anterior eyes. Eyes red-violet, two pairs. Nuchal organ, semicircular nuchal fold, partially covering prostomium (
<figureCitation box="[840,972,1313,1340]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,181,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-26@30.[236,1352,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A) Complete fragmented body. B) Drawing of prostomium, dorsal view. C) Drawing of prostomium, ventral view. D) Prostomium, dorsal view. E) Prostomium, ventral view; arrow indicates Mo. F) Right side of middle segments, arrow indicates dorsal cirrus. G) Dorsal side of the specimen, showing the middorsal line paleae free. H) Parapodium from segment 49. I) Lateral paleae. J) Subunit 1. K) Main palea, arrow indicates finely raised rib. Scales: 20 µm (IJK), 100 µm (BCDEFH), 500 µm (G), 1 mm (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702063/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 14B, D</figureCitation>
). Palps short, ovoid, visible only in ventral view. Mouth fold small, placed between segment 3 and 4 (
<figureCitation box="[766,891,1349,1376]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,181,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-26@30.[236,1352,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A) Complete fragmented body. B) Drawing of prostomium, dorsal view. C) Drawing of prostomium, ventral view. D) Prostomium, dorsal view. E) Prostomium, ventral view; arrow indicates Mo. F) Right side of middle segments, arrow indicates dorsal cirrus. G) Dorsal side of the specimen, showing the middorsal line paleae free. H) Parapodium from segment 49. I) Lateral paleae. J) Subunit 1. K) Main palea, arrow indicates finely raised rib. Scales: 20 µm (IJK), 100 µm (BCDEFH), 500 µm (G), 1 mm (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702063/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 14C, E</figureCitation>
). Pharynx eversible, not exposed, stylet thick.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,881,2024]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Parapodium from segment 49, notochaetae in three main groups (
<figureCitation box="[884,981,1385,1411]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,181,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-26@30.[236,1352,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A) Complete fragmented body. B) Drawing of prostomium, dorsal view. C) Drawing of prostomium, ventral view. D) Prostomium, dorsal view. E) Prostomium, ventral view; arrow indicates Mo. F) Right side of middle segments, arrow indicates dorsal cirrus. G) Dorsal side of the specimen, showing the middorsal line paleae free. H) Parapodium from segment 49. I) Lateral paleae. J) Subunit 1. K) Main palea, arrow indicates finely raised rib. Scales: 20 µm (IJK), 100 µm (BCDEFH), 500 µm (G), 1 mm (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702063/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 14H</figureCitation>
). Notochaetae: lateral group inserted below notaciculum, 1 paleae, very slender and symmetrical, with 1–2 (3) internal ribs (
<figureCitation box="[1005,1093,1421,1447]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,181,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-26@30.[236,1352,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A) Complete fragmented body. B) Drawing of prostomium, dorsal view. C) Drawing of prostomium, ventral view. D) Prostomium, dorsal view. E) Prostomium, ventral view; arrow indicates Mo. F) Right side of middle segments, arrow indicates dorsal cirrus. G) Dorsal side of the specimen, showing the middorsal line paleae free. H) Parapodium from segment 49. I) Lateral paleae. J) Subunit 1. K) Main palea, arrow indicates finely raised rib. Scales: 20 µm (IJK), 100 µm (BCDEFH), 500 µm (G), 1 mm (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702063/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 14I</figureCitation>
); subunit 1, 1 palea, slender and symmetrical, with 9–10 (11) internal ribs (
<figureCitation box="[612,703,1457,1483]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,181,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-26@30.[236,1352,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A) Complete fragmented body. B) Drawing of prostomium, dorsal view. C) Drawing of prostomium, ventral view. D) Prostomium, dorsal view. E) Prostomium, ventral view; arrow indicates Mo. F) Right side of middle segments, arrow indicates dorsal cirrus. G) Dorsal side of the specimen, showing the middorsal line paleae free. H) Parapodium from segment 49. I) Lateral paleae. J) Subunit 1. K) Main palea, arrow indicates finely raised rib. Scales: 20 µm (IJK), 100 µm (BCDEFH), 500 µm (G), 1 mm (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702063/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 14J</figureCitation>
). Main group, 7–9 paleae, broad and symmetrical, with (14) 15–18 (20) internal ribs and 4–5 finely raised ribs (
<figureCitation box="[634,734,1493,1519]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[236,1352,181,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-26@30.[236,1352,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A) Complete fragmented body. B) Drawing of prostomium, dorsal view. C) Drawing of prostomium, ventral view. D) Prostomium, dorsal view. E) Prostomium, ventral view; arrow indicates Mo. F) Right side of middle segments, arrow indicates dorsal cirrus. G) Dorsal side of the specimen, showing the middorsal line paleae free. H) Parapodium from segment 49. I) Lateral paleae. J) Subunit 1. K) Main palea, arrow indicates finely raised rib. Scales: 20 µm (IJK), 100 µm (BCDEFH), 500 µm (G), 1 mm (A)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702063/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 14K</figureCitation>
). Median group, 3 paleae, shorter, slender and asymmetrical; the distal-most palea with 10–11 internal ribs and 3 raised ribs; the next proximal palea smaller with (8) 10 internal ribs and 1 raised rib, and the proximal-most and smallest with 8 internal ribs and 1 raised rib (
<figureCitation box="[1036,1167,1565,1592]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1340,1364]" captionTargetBox="[171,1435,185,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-15@31.[151,1435,181,1316]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A–B) Median paleae. C) Unit 1. D) Unit 2. E–F) Unit 3. G) Unit 4. H) Pygidium, ventral view. I) Complete body, largest specimen (ECOSUR-3219). Scales: 10 µm (CDEFG), 20 µm (AB), 50 µm (H),1 mm (I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702065/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 15A–B</figureCitation>
). All paleae with serrated margins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,881,2024]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Neuropodium conical, smaller than notopodium. Neurochaetae: unit 1, 2 superior spinigers, blades straight and long, 15–16 times longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[488,586,1673,1700]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1340,1364]" captionTargetBox="[171,1435,185,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-15@31.[151,1435,181,1316]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A–B) Median paleae. C) Unit 1. D) Unit 2. E–F) Unit 3. G) Unit 4. H) Pygidium, ventral view. I) Complete body, largest specimen (ECOSUR-3219). Scales: 10 µm (CDEFG), 20 µm (AB), 50 µm (H),1 mm (I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702065/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 15C</figureCitation>
). Unit 2, 6 falcigers with blades straight and short, 1–2 times longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[159,256,1709,1736]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1340,1364]" captionTargetBox="[171,1435,185,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-15@31.[151,1435,181,1316]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A–B) Median paleae. C) Unit 1. D) Unit 2. E–F) Unit 3. G) Unit 4. H) Pygidium, ventral view. I) Complete body, largest specimen (ECOSUR-3219). Scales: 10 µm (CDEFG), 20 µm (AB), 50 µm (H),1 mm (I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702065/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 15D</figureCitation>
). Unit 3, 4 falcigers with blades straight and short, 2 times longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[1056,1178,1709,1736]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1340,1364]" captionTargetBox="[171,1435,185,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-15@31.[151,1435,181,1316]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A–B) Median paleae. C) Unit 1. D) Unit 2. E–F) Unit 3. G) Unit 4. H) Pygidium, ventral view. I) Complete body, largest specimen (ECOSUR-3219). Scales: 10 µm (CDEFG), 20 µm (AB), 50 µm (H),1 mm (I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702065/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 15E–F</figureCitation>
). Unit 4, 2 falcigers with blades straight and medium-sized, 5–6 times longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[812,909,1745,1772]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1340,1364]" captionTargetBox="[171,1435,185,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-15@31.[151,1435,181,1316]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A–B) Median paleae. C) Unit 1. D) Unit 2. E–F) Unit 3. G) Unit 4. H) Pygidium, ventral view. I) Complete body, largest specimen (ECOSUR-3219). Scales: 10 µm (CDEFG), 20 µm (AB), 50 µm (H),1 mm (I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702065/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 15G</figureCitation>
). Blades bidentate, bent distally. Pygidium conical with two anal cirri (
<figureCitation box="[358,456,1781,1808]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1340,1364]" captionTargetBox="[171,1435,185,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-15@31.[151,1435,181,1316]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 15. Bhawatsonia fusa n. sp., holotype (ECOSUR-263). A–B) Median paleae. C) Unit 1. D) Unit 2. E–F) Unit 3. G) Unit 4. H) Pygidium, ventral view. I) Complete body, largest specimen (ECOSUR-3219). Scales: 10 µm (CDEFG), 20 µm (AB), 50 µm (H),1 mm (I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702065/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 15H</figureCitation>
). Oocytes not seen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,881,2024]" box="[199,1406,1817,1844]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1817,1843]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Habitat.</emphasis>
Subtidal (
<quantity box="[400,472,1817,1844]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="m" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 m</quantity>
). Specimens of this species were collected mainly on rocks, and as epibionts of bivalves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1220,1853,1882]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,881,2024]" box="[199,1220,1853,1882]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,343,1853,1879]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Distribution.</emphasis>
From Bahía de los Ángeles, 
<collectingRegion box="[650,811,1853,1879]" country="Mexico" name="Baja California" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Baja California</collectingRegion>
to Barra de Navidad, 
<collectingRegion box="[1043,1114,1853,1879]" country="Mexico" name="Jalisco" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Jalisco</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[1128,1207,1853,1880]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="49.[151,250,1898,1922]" captionTargetBox="[172,1414,917,1868]" captionTargetId="figure-379@49.[166,1422,913,1874]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURE 26. Previous and new records of chrysopetalids in the Tropical Eastern Pacific. Empty symbols indicate historic records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702090/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,881,2024]" lastBlockId="31.[151,1437,1482,1869]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,310,1889,1915]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Cruz-Gómez, 2021" authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2021" box="[321,515,1889,1915]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawatsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusa" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[321,515,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Bhawatsonia fusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[525,589,1889,1915]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[525,589,1889,1915]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, along with 
<taxonomicName box="[734,913,1889,1916]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawatsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[734,873,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Bhawatsonia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authority="Cruz-Gómez, 2021" authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2021" box="[1099,1238,1889,1915]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawatsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis box="[1099,1238,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Bhawatsonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1248,1327,1889,1915]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1248,1327,1889,1915]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
members with broad main paleae and slender median paleae. Specimens of those species can be differentiated by the form of the main paleae; in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cruz-Gómez, 2021" authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2021" box="[323,399,1961,1987]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawatsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusa" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[323,399,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">B. fusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[406,467,1961,1987]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[406,467,1961,1987]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
specimens have broader main paleae, whereas specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1126,1303,1961,1988]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawatsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1126,1265,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Bhawatsonia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
have slightly slender main paleae. In addition, subunit 1 appears to be taxonomically relevant in the members of the new genus. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cruz-Gómez, 2021" authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2021" box="[312,391,1483,1509]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawatsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusa" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[312,391,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">B. fusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[398,462,1483,1509]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[398,462,1483,1509]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
have the subunit 1 with a rounded tip, and a range of internal ribs of 9–10, maximum of 12; whereas, specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[488,674,1518,1545]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawatsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[488,634,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Bhawatsonia</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
have the subunit 1 with an acute tip, and a range of internal ribs of 12–13, maximum of 14.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702063" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5702063" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702063/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" startId="30.[151,250,1845,1869]" targetBox="[236,1352,181,1805]" targetPageId="30">
