<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1482,1869]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
Occurrence with specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Cruz-Gómez" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[546,681,1591,1616]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Paleanotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="purpurea" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[546,681,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">B. purpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[688,790,1591,1617]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[688,790,1591,1617]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is common; however, both species are different. 
<taxonomicName authority="Cruz-Gómez, 2021" authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2021" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawatsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusa" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Bhawatsonia fusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[271,333,1627,1653]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[271,333,1627,1653]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
possess subunit 1 broad, with slightly higher rib number, 9–10, maximum 11; while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Cruz-Gómez" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1274,1407,1627,1652]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Paleanotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="purpurea" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[1274,1407,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">B. purpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
possess subunit 1 slender, with 8–10 internal ribs. Further, the main paleae of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cruz-Gómez, 2021" authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2021" box="[1092,1169,1663,1689]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawatsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusa" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1092,1169,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">B. fusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1175,1237,1663,1689]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1175,1237,1663,1689]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is clearly broader and shorter with slightly reduced rib number, 15–18, maximum 20 internal ribs; meanwhile, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cruz-Gómez, 2021" authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Cruz-Gómez" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1180,1313,1699,1724]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Paleanotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="purpurea" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1180,1313,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">B. purpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1319,1381,1699,1725]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1319,1381,1699,1725]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
possesses slender and longer main paleae with 17–18, maximum 23 interna ribs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1482,1869]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1771,1797]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is made after the Latin singular adjective 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cruz-Gómez" authorityYear="2021" box="[1026,1073,1771,1797]" class="Polychaeta" family="Chrysopetalidae" genus="Bhawatsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fusa">
<emphasis box="[1026,1073,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">fusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(- 
<emphasis box="[1097,1122,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">us</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1135,1179,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">-um</emphasis>
) meaning ‘broad’. The name indicates the broad shape of upper middle section of the main paleae, and it is feminine for matching the genus gender (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[242,375,1843,1869]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" refId="ref37026" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature (The Natural History Museum), London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
, Art. 32.2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
